# Foraging Project — Cursor Rules

Always read README.md at the start of every task for full project context.

## Stack
- Unity 6000.0 LTS, URP, C# 9.0
- New Unity Input System
- Git/GitHub for version control

## Core Rules
- Claude generates Cursor prompts, not direct code edits — when Claude proposes a change, it will be in the form of a prompt for you to paste into Cursor
- When Claude proposes a change, it delivers a Cursor prompt as a single copy-pasteable code block — never as direct code edits
- SessionConfig is the single source of truth for ALL parameters — never hardcode values that a researcher might want to change
- Always add public properties for new SessionConfig fields
- MonoBehaviours use [SerializeField] for inspector-exposed fields
- Use C# Actions for events, not UnityEvents
- Never use FindObjectOfType — use direct references or FindObjectsByType sparingly
- Never modify ProjectSettings/, Packages/, or .meta files unless explicitly asked
- Fruits are runtime-instantiated, never prefab children
- Player is non-kinematic Rigidbody

## Patterns
- New session parameters go in SessionConfig.cs with a [SerializeField] field, private backing field, and public property
- Visual ranges (colors, scales) go in SessionConfig so researchers can tune without code changes
- Procedural systems use sessionConfig.WorldSeed for reproducibility
- Always include fallback values when sessionConfig is null

## File Locations
- Player scripts: Assets/Scripts/Player/
- Bush/tree scripts: Assets/Scripts/Trees/
- World generation: Assets/Scripts/World/
- Session management: Assets/Scripts/Session/
- Shaders: Assets/Shaders/
- Materials: Assets/Materials/
- Prefabs: Assets/Prefabs/
- ScriptableObjects: Assets/ScriptableObjects/

## Additional Constraints  
- Never normalize the reward function output — this is intentional
- Fruit count is always constant across bushes — never vary it per-bush
- Fruit color uses blue→orange axis only — do not introduce red/green hues
- DataLogger output goes to ForagingData/ — never change this path
